HTTP server with Gin framework (NOT implemented)\n- `handlers.go` - HTTP handlers for `/health/*` and invocation endpoints (NOT implemented)\n- `middleware.go` - Concurrency limiting middleware (NOT implemented)\n- `proxy.go` - Reverse proxy implementation (NOT implemented)\n- `cmd/router/main.go` - CLI entry point (NOT implemented)\n\n**Testing:**\n- No unit tests implemented\n- No integration tests implemented\n- Test files exist in other workspaces but not in the target workspace\n\n**Integration Features:**\n- Last-activity annotation updates (defined but not integrated)\n- Health endpoints (not implemented)\n- Reverse proxy to sandbox pods (not implemented)\n- Entry point resolution logic (not implemented)\n- WebSocket support (not implemented)\n\n### Key Files Status\n\n| File | Status | Notes |\n|------|--------|-------|\n| `session_manager.go` | ✅ Implemented | Core session resolution logic |\n| `jwt.go` | ✅ Implemented | JWT signing and key management |\n| `config.go` | ✅ Implemented | Configuration structures |\n| `errors.go` | ✅ Implemented | Error type definitions |\n| `doc.go` | ✅ Implemented | Package documentation |\n| `server.go` | ❌ Deferred | HTTP server main loop |\n| `handlers.go` | ❌ Deferred | Route handlers |\n| `middleware.go` | ❌ Deferred | Concurrency limiting |\n| `proxy.go` | ❌ Deferred | Reverse proxy logic |\n| `types.go` | ❌ Deferred | Additional type definitions |\n\n### Conclusion\n\nAR-010 achieved **scaffold completion** and **partial core implementation** of the session management subsystem. The session manager can resolve sessions and create sandboxes via the workload manager, but the HTTP server infrastructure (which depends on AR-009) was not completed. The change remains in `open` status with all design documentation containing placeholder content.","time":{"start":1775861598363,"end":1775861598363}}}
